<h2 id="pricing-numbers">Pricing and Numbers</h2>

<p>Understanding prices requires knowing how Chinese expresses money. The currency is 人民币 (rénmínbì, RMB) in mainland China and 台币 (táibì, TWD) in Taiwan. Use our <a href="/chinese/tools/number-converter/">Number Converter</a> to practice reading Chinese numbers.</p>

<table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:1.5rem 0;">
  <thead>
    <tr style="background:#fef3c7;">
      <th style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align:left;">Chinese</th>
      <th style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align:left;">Pinyin</th>
      <th style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align:left;">Meaning</th>
      <th style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align:left;">Example</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
