<h2 id="payment">Payment Methods</h2>

<p>Payment culture differs significantly between mainland China and Taiwan. Here's what you need to know:</p>

<div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap:1rem; margin:1.5rem 0;">
  <div style="background:#fef2f2; border:1px solid #fecaca; padding:1.25rem; border-radius:12px;">
    <p style="font-weight:700; font-size:1.1rem; margin:0 0 0.75rem;">🇨🇳 Mainland China</p>
    <ul style="margin:0; padding-left:1.25rem;">
      <li><strong>微信支付</strong> (wēixìn zhīfù) — WeChat Pay</li>
      <li><strong>支付宝</strong> (zhīfùbǎo) — Alipay</li>
      <li><strong>扫码</strong> (sǎo mǎ) — Scan QR code</li>
      <li><strong>现金</strong> (xiànjīn) — Cash (less common)</li>
      <li><strong>刷卡</strong> (shuā kǎ) — Swipe card</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div style="background:#f0f9ff; border:1px solid #bfdbfe; padding:1.25rem; border-radius:12px;">
    <p style="font-weight:700; font-size:1.1rem; margin:0 0 0.75rem;">🇹🇼 Taiwan</p>
    <ul style="margin:0; padding-left:1.25rem;">
      <li><strong>现金</strong> (xiànjīn) — Cash (most common)</li>
      <li><strong>信用卡</strong> (xìnyòngkǎ) — Credit card</li>
      <li><strong>悠游卡</strong> (yōuyóukǎ) — EasyCard</li>
      <li><strong>LINE Pay</strong> — Growing in popularity</li>
      <li><strong>发票</strong> (fāpiào) — Receipt (lottery!)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<p><strong>Payment phrases:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>可以刷卡吗？(Kěyǐ shuā kǎ ma?) — Can I pay by card?</li>
  <li>可以用微信支付吗？(Kěyǐ yòng wēixìn zhīfù ma?) — Can I use WeChat Pay?</li>
  <li>只收现金。(Zhǐ shōu xiànjīn.) — Cash only.</li>
  <li>请给我发票。(Qǐng gěi wǒ fāpiào.) — Please give me a receipt.</li>
  <li>我没有零钱。(Wǒ méiyǒu língqián.) — I don't have change.</li>
</ul>

